org.jetel.ctl

Class TransformLangExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jetel.ctl.TransformLangExecutor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SyntheticNodeVisitor, TransformLangParserConstants, TransformLangParserVisitor

    public class TransformLangExecutor
extends java.lang.Object
implements TransformLangParserVisitor, TransformLangParserConstants
    CTL interpreter implementation. It represents a simple stack-machine performing computation as it traverses the AST tree.

      • getResult

        public java.lang.Object getResult()
        Method which returns result of executing parse tree.
        Basically, it returns whatever object was left on top of executor's stack (usually as a result of last executed expression/operation).
        It can be called repetitively in order to read all objects from stack.
        Returns:
        Object saved on stack or NULL if no more objects are available

      • executeFunction

        public java.lang.Object executeFunction(java.lang.String functionName,
                               java.lang.Object[] arguments,
                               TLType[] dataTypes,
                               DataRecord[] inputRecords,
                               DataRecord[] outputRecords)
                                 throws TransformLangExecutorRuntimeException
        Executes function with specified name declared within CTL code. First performs a lookup to retrieve function declaration. If function is overloaded in CTL, first declared function with such name is executed. Therefore this method should be used only with functions that are not overloaded.
        Parameters:
        functionName - name of function to execute
        arguments - arguments to pass to the executed function
        inputRecords - global array of input records
        outputRecords - global array of output records
        Returns:
        return value of executed function
        Throws:
        TransformLangExecutorRuntimeException - if function with such a name does not exist

      • getDeepCopy

        public static final <T> T getDeepCopy(T value)
        Makes a deep copy of all mutable objects passed as a parameter. Maybe it is not necessary to copy objects of type Date and byte[], because there are no CTL2 functions that can modify a value of type date, byte or cbyte. (ignoring the fact that there was a bug in trunc()). Note that the function duplicates records and creation of records is costly. The function should not be used when copying to an output port - copyByName() or copyByPosition() for record assignment or setValue() for field assignment are used then. The target DataRecord is then responsible for making a copy of the data.
        Parameters:
        value -
        Returns:
        a deep copy of value
